# Implementation Plan: Smart Booking Window Calendar in Edit Timing Popup

## Goal
Replace the plain `<input type="date">` fields in the **Doctor Edit Clinic** and **Admin Edit Clinic** modals with a **calendar-style UI** where:
- Only the days matching the selected open days are **enabled** (clickable)
- All other days are **greyed out / disabled**
- Doctor/admin clicks **Start Date** → all valid dates up to that point are highlighted
- Doctor/admin then clicks **End Date** → range is confirmed, booking window is auto-set
- The "last available date" is always the **last open-day date** within the selected range

---

## All Edge Cases to Handle

| # | Case | Behavior |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | No open days selected yet | Calendar is fully disabled, show warning: "Select open days first" |
| 2 | Only start date clicked, no end date | Start highlighted, waiting for end click |
| 3 | End date clicked before start date | Swap them automatically (or show error) |
| 4 | Range selected but contains zero open days | Impossible (non-open days are disabled, can't be clicked) |
| 5 | Doctor clears open days after setting range | Calendar re-renders, invalid dates become disabled, range is cleared |
| 6 | Open-ended booking window (no end date) | Allow clearing end date — keeps start date only |
| 7 | Clinic 2 (expired window + no remaining open days) | "Book at this Branch" disabled — already fixed ✅ |
| 8 | No booking window set at all (Immediate/Open-ended) | Show "No date restriction" state with a toggle to set one |

